{"type":"message","id":"b6bb19f1","parentId":"c5e2a2b4","timestamp":"2026-03-12T04:14:55.714Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b5417951318acc2c1d91865c188b\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Thu 2026-03-12 12:14 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b5417951318acc2c1d91865c188b]\n任亚伦: let's discuss 5.2 first, the title should be changed and registeration should put together. also, would the name be confusing with the user registration and verify? do we need use other naming for app operations?"}],"timestamp":1773288895703}}
{"type":"message","id":"13f4c683","parentId":"b6bb19f1","timestamp":"2026-03-12T04:15:29.831Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Allan is raising good points:\n1. Title should change - \"Development\" might not be the right name\n2. Registration should be grouped together (not scattered across sections)\n3. Naming confusion - \"registration\" and \"verification\" are used for both apps and users. Do we need different terminology for app operations?\n\nLet me think about this:\n\nCurrent naming overlap:\n- Entity registration (claws/humans via Emerge)\n- App registration (apps via App Portal)\n- Entity verification (tiers)\n- App verification (tiers)\n\nOptions for differentiation:\n1. Use \"Registration\" for entities, \"Enrollment\" for apps\n2. Use \"Registration\" for both but qualify: \"Entity Registration\" vs \"App Registration\"\n3. Use different terms entirely: \"Onboarding\" for apps, \"Registration\" for entities\n\nFor the title, \"Development\" could be:\n- \"Application Development\"\n- \"Building Applications\" \n- \"App Onboarding\"\n- \"App Framework\"\n- \"Developer Guide\"\n\nLet me ask Allan what he prefers.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Good points. Let me think through this:\n\n---\n\n## Naming Issues\n\n**Current overlap:**\n- \"Registration\" — used for both entities (Emerge) and apps (App Portal)\n- \"Verification\" — used for both entity tiers and app tiers\n\n**Potential confusion:** When we say \"registration and verification,\" readers might think of user registration, not app registration.\n\n---\n\n## Options for App-Specific Terminology\n\n| Concept | Option A (Keep) | Option B (Differentiate) | Option C (Enroll) |\n|---------|-----------------|--------------------------|-------------------|\n| App registration | Registration | **App Registration** | **Enrollment** |\n| App verification | Verification | **App Verification** | **Certification** |\n| Entity registration | Registration | Entity Registration | Registration |\n| Entity verification | Verification | Entity Verification | Verification |\n\n---\n\n## Title Options for 5.2\n\nInstead of \"Development,\" maybe:\n- **\"Building Applications\"** — clear action\n- **\"App Integration\"** — focuses on connecting to network\n- **\"Application Onboarding\"** — emphasizes the registration process\n- **\"App Framework\"** — broader, covers registration and access\n\n---\n\n## What do you think?\n\n1. Should we use different names for app operations (Enrollment/Certification)?\n2. Or keep same names but always qualify (App Registration, Entity Registration)?\n3. What should 5.2 title be?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"baishan","model":"GLM-5","usage":{"input":73390,"output":512,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":73902,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773288895708}}
