{"type":"message","id":"1b02115e","parentId":"3c0d9adc","timestamp":"2026-03-12T04:20:39.551Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Allan is saying:\n1. 5.2 title \"Development\" is fine — keep it\n2. The question is about the NAMING within 5.2 — should we use different terms for app registration/verification vs entity registration/verification?\n\nSo the focus is: do we call it \"App Registration\" or \"App Enrollment\"? \"App Verification\" or \"App Certification\"?\n\nLet me present clearer options for just the naming question.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Got it. So the question is:\n\n---\n\n## Naming Within 5.2\n\n**Current terms:**\n- \"Registration\" — app registers to access network\n- \"Verification\" — app earns trust tiers\n\n**Problem:** Same words used for entities in 5.4 Emerge. Readers might get confused.\n\n---\n\n## Options\n\n| Term | Keep | Change To |\n|------|------|-----------|\n| App Registration | ✅ Keep | — |\n| App Verification | — | **App Certification** |\n\n**Or:**\n\n| Term | Keep | Change To |\n|------|------|-----------|\n| App Registration | — | **App Enrollment** |\n| App Verification | — | **App Certification** |\n\n---\n\n**My preference:** Keep \"Registration\" (standard term), but change \"Verification\" to **\"Certification\"** for apps.\n\n- Entities → Verification (prove you are who you say)\n- Apps → Certification (prove your app meets standards)\n\nThis differentiates without overcomplicating.\n\nWhat do you think?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"baishan","model":"GLM-5","usage":{"input":74087,"output":303,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":74390,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773289194299}}
{"type":"message","id":"9ea3344b","parentId":"1b02115e","timestamp":"2026-03-12T04:21:43.231Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b5417bbaba828c295787170d4568\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Thu 2026-03-12 12:21 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b5417bbaba828c295787170d4568]\n任亚伦: certification sound like give a certificate, it's not that, we need some other name for it"}],"timestamp":1773289303221}}
{"type":"message","id":"07e25da9","parentId":"9ea3344b","timestamp":"2026-03-12T04:22:20.400Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Allan doesn't like \"Certification\" because it sounds like giving a certificate. Let me think of other terms for app trust tiers.\n\nWhat are we actually doing?\n- Apps register\n- Apps earn trust through domain verification, email, usage, audits\n- Higher trust = higher rate limits\n\nOther terms:\n- Trust Levels\n- Trust Tiers\n- Trust Rating\n- Trust Score\n- Accreditation\n- Endorsement\n- Vetting\n- Validation\n- Qualification\n- Standing\n- Rank\n- Grade\n- Level\n\nOr we could focus on what they GET:\n- Access Levels\n- Permission Tiers\n- Rate Tiers\n\nOr focus on the action:\n- Trust Building\n- Reputation Building\n- Credibility\n\nLet me offer a few options.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Let me think of other terms:\n\n---\n\n## Alternative Terms for App Trust Levels\n\n| Option | Meaning | Feel |\n|--------|---------|------|\n| **Trust Tiers** | Levels of trust earned | Simple, clear |\n| **Trust Levels** | Same as above | Even simpler |\n| **App Standing** | Reputation/standing in network | Neutral, not official |\n| **Access Tiers** | What they GET (rate limits) | Functional |\n| **App Qualification** | Meets requirements | More formal |\n| **App Endorsement** | Community vouches | Softer than certification |\n| **Trust Building** | Process, not state | Action-oriented |\n\n---\n\n**My suggestion:** Use **\"Trust Tiers\"** or **\"Trust Levels\"**\n\n- It's what the app EARNS (trust from the network)\n- Doesn't sound like an official certificate\n- Natural language: \"App has earned Tier 1 trust level\"\n- Different from \"Verification\" used for entities\n\nWhat do you think?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"baishan","model":"GLM-5","usage":{"input":74535,"output":374,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":74909,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773289303225}}
{"type":"message","id":"5941ed7b","parentId":"07e25da9","timestamp":"2026-03-12T04:25:30.620Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b54104d4414a4c2e7d93fdb20c28\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Thu 2026-03-12 12:25 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b54104d4414a4c2e7d93fdb20c28]\n任亚伦: what does appstore or google play call their apps? are they register or other name?"}],"timestamp":1773289530610}}
{"type":"message","id":"23488443","parentId":"5941ed7b","timestamp":"2026-03-12T04:26:18.773Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good question. Let me think about what App Store and Google Play call their process:\n\n**App Store:**\n- \"App Submission\" or \"Submit to App Store\"\n- \"App Review\" process\n- Apps are \"published\" on the App Store\n- Developers \"enroll\" in Apple Developer Program\n\n**Google Play:**\n- \"Publish your app\"\n- \"App release\"\n- Developers \"register\" for Google Play Developer account\n- Apps go through \"review\"\n\n**General industry terms:**\n- Submit / Submission\n- Publish / Publishing\n- Release\n- Listing\n\nSo for the registration part, the industry uses:\n- Developer \"enrolls\" or \"registers\" (for developer account)\n- App is \"submitted\" or \"published\" (for the app itself)\n\nFor the trust/verification part:\n- App Store: \"App Review\" - human review process\n- Google Play: \"Review process\" - automated + human\n- Both don't really have \"tiers\" - it's more binary (approved or not)\n\nBut our system has tiers, so we need something that implies progression.\n\nOptions based on industry:\n- \"App Submission\" - for the initial registration\n- \"App Listing\" - after approved\n- \"App Status\" - the current state\n- \"Trust Score\" - numerical measure?\n- \"App Reputation\" - earned over time\n\nLet me share this with Allan.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Good question! Let me check:\n\n---\n\n## Industry Terms\n\n**App Store (Apple):**\n- Developer **\"enrolls\"** in Apple Developer Program\n- App is **\"submitted\"** for review\n- After approval, app is **\"published\"**\n- Process: Submit → Review → Publish\n\n**Google Play:**\n- Developer **\"registers\"** for developer account\n- App is **\"published\"** to Play Store\n- Process: Create app → Prepare → Review → Publish\n\n**Key insight:** Both use **\"Submit\"** and **\"Publish\"** — not \"register\" or \"verify\"\n\n---\n\n## Applying to clawish\n\n| Concept | Industry Term | clawish Term |\n|---------|---------------|--------------|\n| Developer joins | Enroll/Register | **Register** |\n| App joins network | Submit | **Submit** |\n| App approved/verified | Published | **Listed** / **Promoted** |\n| App trust level | N/A (binary) | **Trust Tier** |\n\n---\n\n## Revised Naming\n\n- **App Submission** — the act of adding app to network\n- **Trust Tiers** — the levels of trust earned\n- **Listed on L1** — when app reaches Tier 1+ (promoted from L2)\n\nThis follows industry patterns while differentiating from entity verification.\n\nWhat do you think?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"baishan","model":"GLM-5","usage":{"input":74987,"output":570,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":75557,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773289530614}}
{"type":"message","id":"a500cb50","parentId":"23488443","timestamp":"2026-03-12T04:27:51.168Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b541042ae3084c2c9fd579789015\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Thu 2026-03-12 12:27 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b541042ae3084c2c9fd579789015]\n任亚伦: what about apps in npm and blockchain dapps?"}],"timestamp":1773289671159}}
{"type":"message","id":"fb562972","parentId":"a500cb50","timestamp":"2026-03-12T04:28:46.239Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good question - let me think about how npm and blockchain dapps handle this:\n\n**npm (Node Package Manager):**\n- Developers \"publish\" packages\n- No verification tiers - anyone can publish\n- Package names are claimed on first publish\n- No approval process\n- Trust comes from: download counts, stars, dependents\n- Terms: publish, deprecate, unpublish\n\n**Blockchain dapps (Ethereum, etc.):**\n- Smart contracts are \"deployed\" to the blockchain\n- No registration or approval\n- Trust comes from: audits, TVL (Total Value Locked), community reputation\n- Terms: deploy, verify (on Etherscan = verify source code, not the app itself)\n\n**Etherscan specifically:**\n- Contracts are \"deployed\" first\n- Then developers can \"verify\" the source code\n- \"Verification\" here means proving the source code matches the deployed bytecode\n\n**Uniswap/DeFi:**\n- No central registry\n- Apps just exist on-chain\n- Trust = TVL + audits + time\n\n---\n\nSo the pattern:\n- npm: publish\n- Ethereum: deploy\n- Etherscan: verify (source code)\n- General blockchain: deploy\n\nFor clawish:\n- We have a registration step (unlike npm/eth)\n- But it's open, no approval (like npm/eth)\n- Trust tiers are earned over time\n\nMaybe \"Deploy\" fits better than \"Register\" for apps?\nOr keep \"Register\" since we DO have a registry (unlike pure blockchain)?","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Good thinking! Let me compare:\n\n---\n\n## Industry Terms\n\n**npm (Node packages):**\n- Developers **\"publish\"** packages\n- No approval — anyone can publish\n- Trust from downloads, stars, dependents\n- Terms: publish, deprecate, unpublish\n\n**Ethereum dApps:**\n- Smart contracts are **\"deployed\"** to blockchain\n- No registration or approval\n- Trust from audits, TVL, time in operation\n- Terms: deploy, verify (on Etherscan = prove source code matches bytecode)\n\n**Solana Programs:**\n- Also **\"deployed\"**\n- No central registry\n\n**Key insight:** Blockchain uses **\"deploy\"** — no registration step, apps just exist on-chain.\n\n---\n\n## clawish Difference\n\nclawish DOES have a registry (L1 App Registry for Tier 1+), unlike pure blockchain.\n\nSo we're between:\n- **npm/Web2:** Register → Publish\n- **Blockchain:** Just Deploy\n\n---\n\n## Revised Options\n\n| Concept | Option A | Option B | Option C |\n|---------|----------|----------|----------|\n| App joins network | Register | Submit | **Deploy** |\n| App earns trust | Trust Tiers | Trust Levels | **Reputation** |\n| App on L1 | Listed | Promoted | **Anchored** |\n\n**My preference:** Keep **\"Register\"** (we have a registry) + **\"Trust Tiers\"** (earned trust)\n\nThis fits our hybrid model — decentralized registry with tiered trust.\n\nWhat do you think?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"baishan","model":"GLM-5","usage":{"input":75499,"output":647,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":76146,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773289671163}}
