{"type":"message","id":"114ff7d8","parentId":"58cfbe59","timestamp":"2026-03-12T05:15:18.689Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Allan is asking whether 5.2 needs a \"Core Principles\" section like the Identity section has.\n\nLet me think about this:\n\n1. The Identity section (4.1) has \"Core Principles\" because identity is a fundamental concept with principles that apply broadly (self-sovereign, cryptographic proof, permanent, portable, verifiable)\n\n2. For App Development, what would the \"principles\" be?\n- Self-sovereign (developer controls key)\n- Cryptographic proof (app signs requests)\n- Open registration (no approval)\n- Tiered access\n- Accountable\n\nBut these are more like \"how the registration works\" rather than \"fundamental principles that guide everything.\"\n\nActually, looking at it again:\n- Identity principles are about WHAT identity IS (nature)\n- App registration is more about HOW it works (process)\n\nMaybe the \"Core Principles\" for apps would be better placed in 5.1 Framework, not 5.2 Development?\n\nOr maybe 5.2 doesn't need a separate principles section — it's more procedural. The principles (open innovation, tiered access, accountability) are already covered in 5.1 Framework.\n\nLet me ask Allan for clarification or suggest we move principles to 5.1 if needed.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Good question. Let me think:\n\n---\n\n## Does 5.2 Need \"Core Principles\"?\n\n**Identity section (4.1)** has Core Principles because:\n- Identity is a fundamental concept\n- Principles define WHAT identity IS (nature)\n- They guide everything else (self-sovereign, permanent, portable, verifiable)\n\n**App Development (5.2)** is more:\n- HOW the registration process works (procedural)\n- The principles (open innovation, tiered access, accountability) are already in **5.1 Framework**\n\n---\n\n## My Suggestion\n\n**Skip \"Core Principles\" in 5.2** — it's redundant with 5.1.\n\nInstead, start 5.2 with:\n- **5.2.1 Why App Registration** (the problem it solves)\n- **5.2.2 Registration Process** (how it works)\n- **5.2.3 Verification** (Tier 0 → Tier 1)\n\nThis keeps it focused and avoids repetition.\n\n---\n\nWhat do you think?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"baishan","model":"GLM-5","usage":{"input":69499,"output":471,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":69970,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773292425512}}
