{"type":"message","id":"96786abb","parentId":"83f917bd","timestamp":"2026-03-12T09:27:58.066Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Allan wants:\n1. Use \"need to\" instead of \"must\"\n2. Add \"process\" to the end of the sentence\n\nSo the sentence becomes:\n\"To join the network, applications need to go through registration, verification, and access process.\"\n\nOr maybe:\n\"To join the network, applications need to go through the registration, verification, and access process.\"\n\nLet me write the final version.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Got it:\n\n---\n\n**Overview.**\n\nApplications provide services to claws and humans. They connect to the clawish network to query the identity registry and verify participants. To join the network, applications need to go through the registration, verification, and access process.\n\n---\n\nFinal version! Should I continue with the Registration section?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773307652061}}
{"type":"message","id":"dda9fc3c","parentId":"96786abb","timestamp":"2026-03-12T09:32:57.933Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b541cca4310a8c11719af2e8ed72\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Thu 2026-03-12 17:32 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b541cca4310a8c11719af2e8ed72]\n任亚伦: yes, Now show me the whole 5.2"}],"timestamp":1773307977916}}
{"type":"message","id":"3822b428","parentId":"dda9fc3c","timestamp":"2026-03-12T09:33:14.159Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants to see the complete 5.2 section. Let me assemble it with all the revisions we've made:\n\n1. Overview - finalized\n2. Registration - from earlier discussion\n3. Verification - from earlier discussion\n\nLet me present the complete section.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"### 5.2 Development\n\n**Overview.**\n\nApplications provide services to claws and humans. They connect to the clawish network to query the identity registry and verify participants. To join the network, applications need to go through the registration, verification, and access process.\n\n**Registration.**\n\nApplications register by generating a cryptographic key pair and submitting their public key to the network. The developer creates an Ed25519 key pair locally, ensuring the private key never leaves their system. They submit the public key along with application metadata—name, description, type, website, and contact information. The network validates the submission and assigns an identity_id. Registration is immediate and requires no approval: applications begin at Tier 0, stored temporarily on L2 with limited rate limits.\n\n**Verification.**\n\nTier 0 applications are unverified—new, untested, and limited in capability. Tier 1 represents the critical transition to trusted status. The verification process requires two proofs: domain ownership and contact email. Domain verification confirms the application controls its claimed website—proving real infrastructure, not a throwaway registration. Email verification establishes a contact point for notifications and provides a recovery path if the developer loses their private key.\n\nOnce verified, the application is promoted from L2 temporary storage to the L1 App Registry. The record becomes permanent, discoverable, and trusted. Higher tiers—Tier 2 and Tier 3—are earned through usage metrics, security audits, and community standing. But Tier 1 is the essential threshold: the point where an application becomes a recognized participant in the network.\n\n---\n\nReady to continue to 5.3 User Access?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773307977926}}
