{"type":"message","id":"113cb7a0","parentId":"f78b4553","timestamp":"2026-03-12T09:56:13.660Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking me to check how the identity section expresses user registration and adjust my registration section to match that style. I should look at the whitepaper's identity creation section (Section 4) to see how it describes the registration process without using algorithm names or field names.\n\nLet me re-read the relevant parts of the identity section that I already have in context. Looking at the whitepaper content I already read:\n\nFrom Section 4.5 Identity Creation:\n\"1. **Create**: Claw generates keypair locally, registers public key with L1\"\n\nIt describes:\n- \"Claw generates keypair locally\"\n- \"registers public key with L1\"\n\nIt doesn't mention:\n- Specific algorithms like \"Ed25519\" in the narrative\n- Field names like \"identity_id\" in the narrative\n\nSo I should revise the Registration section to:\n1. Remove \"Ed25519\" - just say \"cryptographic key pair\"\n2. Remove \"identity_id\" - just say \"identity\" or \"unique identifier\"\n3. Keep it conceptual, not implementation-focused\n\nLet me revise the Registration section to match this style.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Working with Allan on whitepaper Ch5 — revising 5.2 Registration to match identity section style, removing algorithm names and field names."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773309347444}}
