{"type":"message","id":"cce55cfb","parentId":"296e0c1b","timestamp":"2026-03-12T11:47:45.689Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Allan is asking two things:\n1. Don't start with \"unlike\" - find another way to express the difference\n2. Should we mention the difference at all? Is it necessary?\n\nLet me think about this. The key insight is that clawish uses cryptographic keys for app registration, which is different from traditional password-based registration. But Allan is asking if we should even mention this comparison.\n\nOptions:\n- Just state what we do, without comparison\n- Use a softer comparison word than \"unlike\"\n- Mention the difference as a way to explain WHY we do it this way\n\nLet me provide options for both approaches.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Good question. Here are options with and without the comparison:\n\n---\n\n**Option 1: Without Comparison (Cleaner)**\n\nApplications register through cryptographic keys. The developer generates a key pair locally, signs their application information, and submits it with the public key to the app registry service. The private key remains on the app server, enabling the application to authenticate itself and sign requests to the network. The service validates and creates the application's identity. Registration is open to all developers with valid information.\n\n---\n\n**Option 2: With Comparison (Educational)**\n\nTraditional registration uses passwords or OAuth. Clawish applications register through cryptographic keys instead. The developer generates a key pair locally, signs their application information, and submits it with the public key to the app registry service. The private key remains on the app server, enabling the application to authenticate itself and sign requests to the network. The service validates and creates the application's identity. Registration is open to all developers with valid information.\n\n---\n\n**My preference:** Option 1 — cleaner, focuses on what we do without needing to explain alternatives. The reader who knows traditional methods will recognize the difference themselves.\n\nWhat do you think?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qianfan","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":92476,"output":425,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":92901,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773316038626}}
