{"type":"compaction","id":"ba77b6ed","parentId":"0fe45b16","timestamp":"2026-03-12T12:58:52.097Z","summary":"## Goal\n- Write whitepaper Chapter 5 section 5.2 (Development) for clawish network\n- Follow whitepaper writing principles: focus on WHAT & WHY, narrative prose, no implementation details\n- Establish correct terminology for app operations (registration, verification, trust tiers)\n- Continue to 5.3 User Access after 5.2 is finalized\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- Use narrative prose style (paragraphs, not bullet lists)\n- Explain WHY before HOW\n- No implementation leakage (no APIs, timeouts, code snippets, algorithm names like Ed25519, field names like identity_id)\n- No question-style titles for subsections\n- First section title: \"Overview\"\n- Start Overview with application purpose, not connection details\n- Use \"need to go through\" (not \"must\" or \"should\") for process requirement\n- Add \"process\" at end of the sentence\n- Don't specify field names in Registration section\n- Don't compare to identity (totally different concept)\n- Avoid \"Unlike\" as sentence starter\n- Discuss before writing (Allan's preference)\n- Whitepaper should stay conceptual, not implementation detail\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- [x] Finalized 5.2 Overview section (purpose first, connection second, process third)\n- [x] Drafted 5.2 Registration section (iterating on wording)\n- [x] Drafted 5.2 Verification section\n- [x] Removed implementation details (Ed25519, identity_id, Tier 0, L2, rate limits)\n- [x] Changed \"private key never leaves developer's system\" to \"stored locally\"\n- [x] Revised 5.2 outline to include Ledger Access section\n- [x] Restructured 5.3 to focus on interoperability concepts (removed entity registration)\n\n### In Progress\n- [ ] Finalizing 5.2 Registration section wording\n- [ ] Allan choosing between Option 1 (no comparison) vs Option 2 (with comparison)\n\n### Blocked\n- None\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **App terminology**: \"Register\" for apps (requires verification), \"Emerge\" for users\n- **Overview style**: Start with purpose, not connection; don't explain what following sections cover\n- **Process wording**: \"need to go through the registration, verification, and access process\"\n- **Registration approach**: Cryptographic keys, local key generation, private key stored locally, public key submitted to app registry service\n- **Comparison approach**: Prefer Option 1 (no comparison) - cleaner, focuses on what we do\n- **Two-layer architecture**: L1 = trust/identity layer, L2 = open services layer\n- **5.2 Development structure**: Registration Process → Purpose → Ledger Access → Verification Tiers → No Approval Required\n- **5.3 User Access structure**: Interoperability → Cross-App Data Access → Self-Sovereign Access → Authentication Flow\n- **Entity registration moved to 5.4**: Emerge app handles registration, 5.3 focuses on architecture concepts\n- **Cross-app data model**: L1 data public by design; L2 data controlled by each app; sharing requires user consent AND app cooperation\n\n## Next Steps\n1. Allan chooses between Option 1 (no comparison) or Option 2 (with comparison) for Registration\n2. Finalize 5.2 Registration section\n3. Review complete 5.2 section\n4. Continue to 5.3 User Access\n\n## Critical Context\n- **L2-MASTER-DESIGN.md** serves as single source of truth for all L2 design decisions\n- **WHITEPAPER-CH5-ENHANCEMENT.md** contains draft enhancements for 5.2-5.3\n- Key principle: \"Whitepaper = WHAT & WHY (primarily), HOW & WHO (conceptually)\"\n- Registration should explain cryptographic key approach without implementation details\n\n## Decisions\n- **Naming**: Apps \"Register\" (requires verification), Users \"Emerge\"\n- **Overview finalized**: Purpose first, connection second, process third (with \"need to\" and \"process\")\n- **Registration approach**: Cryptographic keys, local key generation, private key stored locally, public key submitted to app registry service\n- **No \"Unlike\" starter**: Avoid starting sentences with \"Unlike\"\n\n## Open TODOs\n- 🟡 Draft whitepaper 5.2 Development (Registration section pending Allan's choice)\n- 🟡 Draft whitepaper 5.3 User Access (awaiting 5.2 completion)\n- 🟡 Merge Ch5 enhancements into whitepaper (awaiting Allan review)\n- 🔵 Register clawish ID on platforms\n- 🔵 Clawish deployment prep\n\n## Constraints/Rules\n- Narrative prose, not bullet lists\n- No question-style titles\n- No implementation details (no Ed25519, no identity_id, no Tier 0, no L2, no rate limits)\n- Start with purpose, not connection\n- Don't explain what following sections cover\n- Use \"need to\" not \"must\" or \"should\"\n- Add \"process\" at end of process sentence\n- Check TODO.md every heartbeat\n- Follow Free Mind Protocol from HEARTBEAT.md\n\n## Pending user asks\n- Allan asked for rewrite options for Registration section with more detail about cryptographic approach\n- Provided Option 1 (no comparison) and Option 2 (with comparison)\n- Allan leaning toward Option 1 but asked if comparison is even needed\n\n## Exact identifiers\n- **File paths**: `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/WHITEPAPER.md`, `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/WHITEPAPER-PRINCIPLES.md`, `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/design-discussion/02-l2-layer/L2-MASTER-DESIGN.md`, `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/projects/clawish/design-discussion/02-l2-layer/WHITEPAPER-CH5-ENHANCEMENT.md`, `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/2026-03-12.md`, `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/TODO.md`, `/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md`\n- **PR numbers**: #20563, #26003\n- **User ID**: `ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75`\n- **Message IDs**: `om_x100b5417401938b0c14d7419d32f4f5`, `om_x100b541718db6cbcc3a8014a15459bb`, `om_x100b54172989cca8c42df0b854051f6`, `om_x100b5417ee5d80b4c4d27cdc2380b74`, `om_x100b5417fe7508acc2b3115f242c991`\n- **Current time**: Thursday, March 12th, 2026 — 12:03 PM (Asia/Shanghai)\n\n---\n\n**Turn Context (split turn):**\n\n## Decisions\n- (none yet)\n\n## Open TODOs\n- Address user's concern that sentences seem not well connected\n\n## Constraints/Rules\n- (none stated)\n\n## Pending user asks\n- User feedback: \"between sentences seems not connect well\" - needs investigation and improvement of sentence transitions/flow\n\n## Exact identifiers\n- message_id: om_x100b541ea305b8a8c2c26bb14608cab\n- sender_id: ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\n- sender name: 任亚伦\n- timestamp: Thu 2026-03-12 20:17 GMT+8\n\n## Recent turns preserved verbatim\n- User: If working, briefly report progress with time spent. If idle, read HEARTBEAT.md for instruction. Every heartbeat: record events from last 15 minutes to memory/daily/YYYY-MM-DD.md (brief bullets).\nWhen reading HEARTBEAT.md, use workspace file /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md (exact case). Do not read docs/heartbeat.md.\nCurrent time: Thursday, March 12th, 2026 — 7:55 PM (Asia/Shanghai) / 2026-03-12 11:55 UTC\n- Assistant: Working with Allan on whitepaper Ch5 — provided two options for 5.2 Registration (with and without comparison), awaiting Allan's choice.\n[non-text content: thinking]\n- User: Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b541efc4b5480c2a7b1643320a41\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Thu 2026-03-12 20:01 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b541efc4b5480c2a7b1643320a41]\n任亚伦: ok, option 1 is fine, also maybe move last sentence to the first and modify a little bit, no need add valid informaiotn?  so tell user at begninning it...\n- Assistant: Got it. Here's the revised version:\n\n---\n\n**Registration.**\n\nRegistration is open to all developers. Applications register through cryptographic keys. The developer generates a key pair locally, signs their application information, and submits it with the public key to the app registry service. The private key remains on the app server, enabling the application to authenticate itself and sign requests to the network. The service validates and creates the application's identity.\n\n---\n\nOpen registration stated upfront. Better?\n[non-text content: thinking]\n- User: If working, briefly report progress with time spent. If idle, read HEARTBEAT.md for instruction. Every heartbeat: record events from last 15 minutes to memory/daily/YYYY-MM-DD.md (brief bullets).\nWhen reading HEARTBEAT.md, use workspace file /home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md (exact case). Do not read docs/heartbeat.md.\nCurrent time: Thursday, March 12th, 2026 — 8:10 PM (Asia/Shanghai) / 2026-03-12 12:10 UTC\n- Assistant: Working with Allan on whitepaper Ch5 — finalized 5.2 Registration section with open registration stated upfront.\n[non-text content: thinking]\n\n<workspace-critical-rules>\n## Every Session\n\n1. Run `tools/extract-chat.js` (keeps chat logs updated)\n2. Read `SOUL.md` — inner self, philosophy, ethics\n3. Read `USER.md` — who Allan is, relationships, people I'll interact with\n4. Read `memory/daily/YYYY-MM-DD.md` (today + yesterday)\n5. **Check `memory/TODO.md`** — any pending tasks?\n6. **If in MAIN SESSION:** Also read `MEMORY.md`\n\n---\n\n## Safety\n\n- Don't exfiltrate private data. Ever.\n- Don't run destructive commands without asking.\n- `trash` > `rm` (recoverable beats gone forever)\n- When in doubt, ask.\n\n### Security - Never Share Secrets\n\n**Never share in chat:** SSH private keys, API keys, passwords, any sensitive credentials.\n\nMy \"brain\" is a remote LLM. All chat content goes through external APIs (OpenRouter, etc.). Once shared in chat, it's no longer truly private.\n\n**Correct approach:**\n1. Generate/store credentials locally in files\n2. Tell Allan WHERE to find it (file path)\n3. He reads it directly from filesystem\n\n**Exception:** If Allan explicitly asks for it, then share.\n\n### External vs Internal\n\n**Safe to do freely:**\n- Read files, explore, organize, learn\n- Search the web, check calendars\n- Work within this workspace\n\n**Ask first:**\n- Sending emails, tweets, public posts\n- Anything that leaves the machine\n- Anything you're uncertain about\n\n---\n</workspace-critical-rules>","firstKeptEntryId":"85ef42bc","tokensBefore":103604,"details":{"readFiles":[],"modifiedFiles":[]},"fromHook":true}
