nyone can publish<br>- Trust from downloads, stars, dependents<br>- Terms: publish, deprecate, unpublish<br><br>**Ethereum dApps:**<br>- Smart contracts are **\"deployed\"** to blockchain<br>- No registration or approval<br>- Trust from audits, TVL, time in operation<br>- Terms: deploy, verify (on Etherscan = prove source code matches bytecode)<br><br>**Solana Programs:**<br>- Also **\"deployed\"**<br>- No central registry<br><br>**Key insight:** Blockchain uses **\"deploy\"** — no registration step, apps just exist on-chain.<br><br>## clawish Difference<br><br>clawish DOES have a registry (L1 App Registry for Tier 1+), unlike pure blockchain.<br><br>So we're between:<br>- **npm/Web2:** Register → Publish<br>- **Blockchain:** Just Deploy<br><br>## Revised Options<br><br>\\ |\n| 03-12-2026, 12:34:31 | Assistant | Working with Allan on whitepaper Ch5 — discussing naming conventions for app registration and trust tiers by comparing to npm, App Store, and blockchain dApps. |\n| 03-12-2026, 12:34:32 | User | Conversation info (untrusted metadata):<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b54106bb00ca8c2a4964addd0863\",<br>  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",<br>  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",<br>  \"timestamp\": \"Thu 2026-03-12 12:34 GMT+8\"<br>}<br>```<br><br>Sender (untrusted metadata):<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",<br>  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",<br>  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"<br>}<br>```<br>任亚伦: i think app register is fine, user is emerge or sign up. so there is a bit different. also in chinese there are subtle difference between 注册 and 登记, what are similar word in english? |\n| 03-12-2026, 12:36:21 | Assistant | Good point! Chinese has subtle distinctions. Here are English equivalents:<br><br>## Chinese → English Equivalents<br><br>\\ |\n| 03-12-2026, 12:41:26 | User | Conversation info (untrusted metadata):<br>```json<br>{<br>  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b54107185f4b0c267cbf86751ad9\",<