{"type":"message","id":"5bea36ea","parentId":"82864e4d","timestamp":"2026-03-12T14:44:20.618Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Got it. Let me revise:\n\n**Verification.**\n\nAfter registration, applications begin as Tier 0 (unverified) on L2. This is the starting point for all new applications. To become trusted, applications need to go through verification. Tier 1 represents the critical transition to trusted status. The verification process requires two proofs: domain ownership and contact email. Domain verification confirms the application controls its claimed website—proving real infrastructure, not a throwaway registration. Email verification establishes a contact point for notifications and provides a recovery path if the developer loses their private key.\n\nOnce verified, the application is promoted from L2 temporary storage to the L1 App Registry. The record becomes permanent, discoverable, and trusted. Higher tiers—Tier 2 and Tier 3—are earned through usage metrics, security audits, and community standing. But Tier 1 is the essential threshold: the point where an application becomes a recognized participant in the network.\n\n---\n\nBetter flow now?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":68799,"output":196,"cacheRead":8256,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":77251,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773326618399}}
