{"type":"message","id":"28e32c6c","parentId":"c7d93000","timestamp":"2026-03-12T15:07:15.355Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Got it. So the structure is:\n\n**Verification** = Binary (Verified ✓)\n- Domain + email verification\n- L2 → L1 promotion\n\n**App Quality** = Earned through usage, reputation, audits\n- Separate from verification\n- Determines discovery, ranking, capabilities\n\nThis is cleaner and more descriptive than \"merit\" or \"score.\"\n\nShould we include App Quality in the 5.2 outline, or save it for later discussion? The current outline has:\n\n1. Registration Process\n2. Purpose of Registration\n3. Ledger Access\n4. Verification Tiers → **Verification** (binary)\n5. No Approval Required\n\nDo we add **App Quality** as a new section, or leave it out for now since it's not fully designed yet?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":86558,"output":159,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":86717,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773328015236}}
