{"type":"message","id":"ff8b6ee1","parentId":"654d0517","timestamp":"2026-03-12T15:19:15.800Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good question. Let me think about this:\n\n**Current Verification section mentions:**\n- Domain ownership\n- Contact email\n\n**Arguments for keeping:**\n- Explains WHAT verification is (not just \"verified\")\n- Shows the concept (prove infrastructure + contact)\n- Not too detailed (no specific implementation like DNS TXT records)\n\n**Arguments for removing:**\n- Implementation might change\n- Could use different methods later\n- Whitepaper should stay conceptual\n\n**My recommendation:** Keep it conceptual but vague:\n\n**Option A (current):**\n> \"The verification process requires two proofs: domain ownership and contact email.\"\n\n**Option B (more conceptual):**\n> \"The verification process requires proof of infrastructure ownership and a verified contact method.\"\n\n**Option C (most conceptual):**\n> \"The verification process requires proofs that establish the application's legitimacy and provide a recovery path.\"\n\nI think **Option B** is a good balance — explains the concept (infrastructure + contact) without being too specific about the method.\n\nWhat do you think?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":79879,"output":206,"cacheRead":8064,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":88149,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773328688987}}
