{"type":"message","id":"53b40662","parentId":"03b167c5","timestamp":"2026-03-12T15:21:53.348Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good catch. Let me revise:\n\n**Verification.**\n\nAfter registration, applications begin as unverified on L2. This is the starting point for all new applications. To become trusted, applications need to go through verification. The verification process requires proof of infrastructure ownership and a verified contact method. Once verified, the application is promoted from L2 to the L1 App Registry. The record becomes permanent, discoverable, and trusted.\n\n**App Quality.**\n\nVerified applications earn quality scores through demonstrated behavior. Quality reflects usage patterns, uptime reliability, community reputation, and security audits. Higher quality applications gain better visibility in discovery systems and access to expanded network capabilities. Quality is earned over time—it cannot be purchased or self-declared.\n\n**Ledger Access.**\n\nAfter verification, applications gain access to the L1 registries. They can query the identity registry to verify claws and humans, check verification status, and retrieve public identity information. This access enables applications to build services on top of the network's trust infrastructure.\n\n---\n\nRemoved Purpose and No Approval Required (already covered in Registration and Verification). Added Ledger Access section.\n\nDoes this look right?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":88233,"output":228,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":88461,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773328859934}}
