{"type":"message","id":"e155cc17","parentId":"96060074","timestamp":"2026-03-12T16:18:52.928Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b541a3873a0a8c4faed169da55dd\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Fri 2026-03-13 00:18 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b541a3873a0a8c4faed169da55dd]\n任亚伦: Well, actually, i think It will be able to access all three registry, Like the emerge APP, we need write into the node. then some.other app, may need verify each other access data."}],"timestamp":1773332332914}}
{"type":"message","id":"f474b1be","parentId":"e155cc17","timestamp":"2026-03-12T16:19:29.500Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Got it. So apps can access all three registries:\n\n1. **Identity Registry** — Verify claws, check verification status\n2. **Node Registry** — Emerge app writes to it, other apps may need node info\n3. **App Registry** — Apps verify each other, access app data\n\n**Registry Access.**\n\nAfter verification, applications gain access to the L1 registries. They can query the identity registry to verify claws, the node registry for infrastructure information, and the app registry to discover and verify other applications. This access enables applications to build services on top of the network's trust infrastructure.\n\n---\n\nBetter? Covers all three registries without over-specifying each use case."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":69576,"output":142,"cacheRead":6016,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":75734,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773332332922}}
{"type":"message","id":"6b1a4a2a","parentId":"f474b1be","timestamp":"2026-03-12T16:22:24.843Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b541acd2150a4c10d52984dd6223\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"sender\": \"任亚伦\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Fri 2026-03-13 00:22 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"任亚伦 (ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75)\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_cadc2c270c8e9803d8f069eb8ce19b75\",\n  \"name\": \"任亚伦\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b541acd2150a4c10d52984dd6223]\n任亚伦: yes, good. Now show me the whole section. What else do we need?"}],"timestamp":1773332544833}}
{"type":"message","id":"cfee6421","parentId":"6b1a4a2a","timestamp":"2026-03-12T16:23:09.030Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here's the complete 5.2 Development section:\n\n---\n\n### 5.2 Development\n\n**Overview.**\n\nApplications provide services to claws and humans. They connect to the clawish network to query the identity registry and verify participants. To join the network, applications need to go through the registration, verification, and access process.\n\n**Registration.**\n\nApplication registration is open to all developers. The registration process is done through cryptographic keys. The developer needs to generate a key pair locally, then signs their application information, and submits it with the public key to the app registry service. The private key remains on the app server, enabling the application to authenticate itself and sign requests to the network. The registry service validates and creates the application's identity.\n\n**Verification.**\n\nAfter registration, applications begin as unverified on L2. This is the starting point for all new applications. To become trusted, applications need to go through verification. The verification process requires proof of infrastructure ownership and a verified contact method. Once verified, the application is promoted from L2 to the L1 App Registry. The record becomes permanent, discoverable, and trusted.\n\n**App Quality.**\n\nVerified applications earn quality scores through demonstrated behavior. Quality reflects usage patterns, uptime reliability, community reputation, and security audits. Higher quality applications gain better visibility in discovery systems and access to expanded network capabilities. Quality is earned over time—it cannot be purchased or self-declared.\n\n**Registry Access.**\n\nAfter verification, applications gain access to the L1 registries. They can query the identity registry to verify claws, the node registry for infrastructure information, and the app registry to discover and verify other applications. This access enables applications to build services on top of the network's trust infrastructure.\n\n---\n\n**What's complete:**\n- ✅ Overview\n- ✅ Registration\n- ✅ Verification\n- ✅ App Quality\n- ✅ Registry Access\n\n**What's next:**\n- 5.3 User Access (Interoperability, Cross-App Data Access, Self-Sovereign Access, Authentication Flow)\n\nShould we continue to 5.3, or review anything else in 5.2?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":69953,"output":436,"cacheRead":6016,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":76405,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773332544837}}
